me was  Giovanni . He had a pleasant, ordinary life as a child and young man, but after two serious illnesses, a period of military service, and a year as a prisoner of war in Perugia, he turned from the world and devoted himself to caring for the poor and sick. He was joined by groups of disciples, calling themselves ‘minor friars’ (<i>friari minores</i>). The main features of the Franciscan rule are humility, poverty, and love for all living creatures. The given name occurs occasionally in England as early as  1300 , and more frequently from the early 16th century, when there was a surge of admiration for, and imitation of, Italian Renaissance culture."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":43,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Francis Ticknall was born about 1412, in Newhall, Derbyshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Francis Ticknall."},"et":{"about 1412–":"umbes 1412–Surnud","1417–Female":"1417–Surnud","1438–1489":"1438–1489","1412–Male":"1412–Surnud","1412":"1412","1489":"1489","1455":"1455","about 1438":"umbes 1438","about 1412":"umbes 1412","1417":"1417","1438":"1438","Newhall, Derbyshire, England":"Newhall, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1412–":"noin 1412–Kuollut","1417–Female":"1417–Kuollut","1438–1489":"1438–1489","1412–Male":"1412–Kuollut","1412":"1412","1489":"1489","1455":"1455","about 1438":"noin 1438","about 1412":"noin 1412","1417":"1417","1438":"1438","Newhall, Derbyshire, England":"Newhall, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1412–":"en